gomodel:SYNGO_1774  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: 2/11/2017 Pim\n- Authors show N-cadherin labeling of the synaptic cleft outside of the area defined by the active zone and PSD (Fig.7E). The authors interpret this labeling as to originate from N-cadherin proteins intergral to the plasm membranes of the pre- and postsynaptic compartments. They do this based on the observations that 1) N-cadherin interacts with intracellular alphaN-catenin protein (Fig.8) and that 2) alphaN-catenin is present at the interface of the presynaptic as well as the postsynaptic plasma membrane at a region reminiscent of the N-cadherin area (Fig.7F; no double staining was used).\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and methods. \"For adult mice those older than 1 mo were used.........The days when the animals were born was regarded as postnatal day 0. The study also used chicken tissue but figures for the annotation involved mouse tissue." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1774" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9031" .

